  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Delivery Manager",
  "description": "<p>Responsibilities:</p><p>·      \nWork closely with APAC Leaders, responsible in shaping IT/AV technologies and services strategies.·      \nEstablish E2E Audio-Visual (AV) business and solely built all workflows, processes, and written Playbook for sales, project, and customer service.<br />Lead project planning activities, including scope definition, resource allocation, and timeline estimation, to ensure alignment with project goals and objectives.</p><p>Develop detailed project plans, schedules, and milestones, and track progress against project timelines to ensure timely delivery of deliverables.</p><p>Identify and mitigate project risks, issues, and dependencies proactively, and escalate critical issues to senior management as needed.</p><p>Facilitate collaboration and communication between cross functional teams, including mobile developers, backend developers, frontend engineers, etc to ensure alignment on project priorities, deliverables, and timelines.</p><p>Monitor project deliverables and outcomes, ensuring adherence to quality standards and take corrective action as needed to address deviations from the project plan.</p><p>Serve as the primary point of contact for project related inquiries, requests, escalation.</p><p><br /></p><p>Requirements:</p><p>Proven experience in project management or delivery management roles in media industry with a track record of successfully delivering complex projects on time and within budget, with at least 10 years of relevant working experience.</p><p>Strong understanding of project management methodologies, frameworks, and best practices, including Agile, Scrum, or Waterfall, and the ability to adapt approaches based on project requirements.</p><p>Analytical and problem-solving skills, with the ability to identify risks, issues, and dependencies early in the project lifecycle and develop mitigation strategies to address them.</p><p>Experience with project management tools and software, such as Jira, Monday.com, or Gitlab for project planning, tracking, and reporting.</p><p>Passion for driving continuous improvement, innovation, and excellence in project delivery, with a focus on delivering value to customers and stakeholders.</p>",
